data.name: infRecord1
data.value: The first data field MUST be +INFO. The second data field is the e-mail address of the submitter. The third data field is a password that may be required in the future; at the present time simply use password for this field. The fourth data field is the nature of the data records. For FreeREG this must be SEQUENCED. The Fifth data field is the type of register information being submitted. It can be one of BAPTISMS, MARRIAGES, BURIALS.The sixth data field identifies the character set used in the file. If you used a windows application such as Excel to create the file then you may leave this field blank. If you used a DOS application such as SpeedREG then use one of cp437, cp850, cp852 for this field. (Type MODE to find out which one). Macintosh users should enter the word macintosh into the chset field. Others chset options can be identified by contacting the project manager.

data.name: infRecord2
data.value: The first data field must be #. The second data field should be CCC. The third data field is the submitter's name. The fourth data field is the group with which the submitter is working. The fifth data field is the file name of the transcribed file. The file name must consist of: [three letter Chapman code for the county][a three letter placename code assigned by the person uploading the file][BA|BU|MA][part number, if any].CSV. The file name should be all upper case. ( The sixth data field contains the date of transcription (dd-mon-yyyy)
